I learned so much about myself and directing by being thrown into this process and supported throughout it. The care that the @therealhartbeat team put into every part of the fellowship made it unforgettable. I’m grateful that this will always be my first directing experience. My cast is comprised of warriors! They really showed up for me 😭 I couldn’t imagine it any other way with any other group of people. 💖 PS. this is also my rap debut 🤣 when you need a 🔥 song, sometimes you just have to write it and rap on it yourself! 

📝extra little Journal entry: 
We shot this film in less than 24 hours, and I learned why preparation is so important!￼ I spent hours with my DP going over our look and shots. Made detailed look books for different departments. Traveled home to Atlanta to grab inspiration from beauty supply stores there. Sought mentorship and shadowed some of my favorite directors. Filmed on location at a Black Owned Beauty Supply Store in Inglewood, called Glow & Flow, which I loved! ￼￼Showed up to my editor’s studio and worked with her in person as much as I could. I even wrote and performed a rap in a day with studio time I paid for myself ￼when we couldn’t get a particular song I wanted. ￼We needed one more actor for a quick cameo, so I jumped in on that too! it to be the first but not the last time I directed something. AND I wanted to do justice to Danielle’s vision! I put my whole self into this so that I could get the most out of it. 

HEY BOO on Peacock
Written by: Danielle Solomon
Directed by: Logan Browning 
DP: Kristopher Carillo
Edited by: Lilly Wild
Produced by: Thai Randolph, Candace Wilson Cherry 
Starring: Ayona Clemons, Alesha Renee, Kaye Winks, Nicolette Ellis, LaShonda Reese

#SoulfulSunday.  Today has been so heavy.  My heart aches. I've cried for this young man and his family. I've cried for my own grandsons and husband. I've donated to his Go Fund Me. I've sat on hold for hours calling. I've asked God why.  There are no answers and I feel helpless but the very least we can do is share this and raise the national awareness of what continues to happen to our boys. If you feel so inclined, please repost and donate to his fund, link is in @shaunking bio.  Maybe we will find peace in the next life because we are so hated in this one!  Repost:  @shaunking 🚨His name is Ralph Yarl. And I’m now working with his family.⁣
⁣
He’s a brilliant, talented, kind, outgoing 16 year old boy from a wonderful family who was shot twice by a white man when Ralph rang the doorbell to pick up his young siblings. ⁣
⁣
➡️➡️➡️➡️ Police said that Ralph was picking up his siblings at a house on N.E. 115th Terrace, but mistakenly went to a house on N.E. 115th Street in Kansas City, Missouri. ⁣
⁣
And the white homeowner shot Ralph once through the glass front door. Then shot him again in the head to make sure he was dead. ⁣
⁣
By a complete miracle, Ralph has SURVIVED and is recovering. ⁣
⁣
🤬 This homeowner needs to be arrested IMMEDIATELY. He should have been arrested the day this happened. ⁣
⁣
🤬🤬🤬THIS IS NOT A MAN STANDING HIS GROUND. This is NOT a stand your ground case. ⁣
⁣
A young Black boy HAS THE RIGHT to accidentally go to 115th Street instead of 115th Terrace WITHOUT BEING SHOT. Period. ⁣
⁣
I’ve helped this dear family secure attorneys @leemerrittesq & @attorneycrump and we are prepared to make sure this family gets justice and accountability. ⁣
⁣
Police took the shooter in, THEN LET HIM GO. Let him destroy most of the evidence, and have not charged him.⁣
⁣
➡️ WE WILL NOT LET THIS STAND.⁣
⁣
🚨🚨🚨🚨 ACTION STEPS.⁣
⁣
1. Email the prosecutor, Zachary Thompson:⁣
⁣
prosecutor@claycopa.com⁣
⁣
2. Call him @ 816-736-8300⁣
⁣
3. Call the Kansas City Police Department @: 816.234.5111 & 816.234.5000⁣
⁣
And let him know this is NOT a stand your ground case and that charges MUST be filed here in the shooting of 16 year old Ralph Yarl.

If you’ve ever visited @silversandsgrenada then you know the feeling you get when you enter the lobby and look out at the serene 330ft infinity pool that leads directly to the sweet sands of #GrandAnseBeach 

This breathtaking experience inspired us to explore the idea of hosting the first steps of our marriage journey as #WalkersByFaith at this property. We wanted to invite our loved ones to delight in paradise, and feel the pulse of a place and a people that exude pure love. 

Thanks to the masterminds of @exhilarateexperiential @diannvalentine and our @silversandsgrenada family, they enlisted local hands alongside Diann’s team to build a custom 330ft aisle for me to walk down, and for us to take our first steps as #WalkersOnWater. After the ceremony it was transformed into a gorgeous reception area and dance floor. 

The outcome of this effort blew our minds. It was unquestionably the hard working and heart working hands of truly amazing people and professionals that ensured it was executed with excellence. 

SEE the BTS on the build-out. Video is courtesy of @silversandsgrenada

📷 : @stanlophotography

Change is good but it's also very hard.  I've been exploring and finding my next chapter for a while now and settled on beauty 3 years ago.  My reputation and success has not been transferable so I've literally had to start over.  The people I know and love the most have not been as supportive as I thought they would be.  I know Amazon is easier but...I digress.  It's been 3 years and I still don't take a salary but I know where I'm going and I know what I'm building.  I LOVE servicing and representing everyday, hard-working black women because we deserve just as much respect and care as my luxury clients.  @slayyy_hair_ is the latest step into  carving out my own beauty lane.  I chose braiding hair because it is a low cost solution for working class women but also one of the most toxic products in beauty.  Slayyy is a healthier solution and I did it for the countless Glow Getters that visit and support our stores daily.  I see you and this one is for you.  Thank U! #DVDidIt  Repost @slayyy_hair_

This birthday means so much because for the last 3 years, I've been charting my next chapter. Opening @glowandflowbeauty, securing a 2nd location, buying a salon and then closing a salon, developing @slayyy_hair_ and launching it and watching women across the US place order after order, juggling multi-million dollar weddings and designing homes around the globe.  Keeping my head down, nose to the grind, minding my business and drinking my water.  Being who I need to be for my clients, the amazing women that trust me with sooooooo much.  Striving to be everything that @riann_valentine and her babies need me to be and making sure my love @damonhaley knows that he is still the love of my life while still making time for my fashion obsession and random European excursions has been a lot.  Praying for discernment and laser focus during this season.  I've made some money. I've lost some money.  My circle got smaller and tighter.  My business partners have kept 10 toes down trusting my vision and believing that we can do something extraordinary.  I've had an amazing career and I've done great things but this next chapter is legacy building.  Thank you for coming along for the ride! Thank you Lord for this beautiful life! #DVDidIt #CancerSeason July 7, 1970 and aging like fine wine!

When I'm designing a residential project, I always start with the 'Wow Factor' that one element that anchors the home and I know is going to get the most gasps when anyone enters the space.  Sometimes that element is swimming in my head and must be fabricated and other times it is found in a design showroom and speaks to me like nothing else. I'm so excited to join @kendrabrackenferguson and @btfoundersstudio for the Black Beauty Bazaar in Martha's Vineyard this week.  A room full of black beauty founders, beauty bosses and the powerful leaders and investors that build these brands is my idea of a good time!  @slayyy_hair_ is so proud to offer women of color a better alternative to the traditional synthetic options that is non-toxic and itch-free.  We are revolutionizing the toxic products we put in our hair and we are here to stay! #DVDidIt

Reminiscing about an amazing few days in Martha's Vineyard with the @btfoundersstudio introducing @slayyy_hair_ to some folks who matter.  I've always believed that black people are enough and if we can just have a seat at our own tables we would be just fine.  @kendrabrackenferguson proved that and I am inspired beyond words.  Onward! #DVDoingIt

#SoulfulSunday @slayyy_hair_ officially launched on July 1st and we are now having conversations I never imagined we would have this soon. Ms. Yolanda of @candis.beauty.supplies in Las Vegas was the first retail account in Nevada to buy in @slayyy_hair_.  I shared with her how important it was to me that SLAYYY would initially only be available at black-owned beauty retail locations because that's how we slowly take back the industry that black women built.  That's how we buy back the block.  That's how we create a safe space for our children...we own our own community.  She didn't hesitate and stood tall when others gave me a long list of reasons why they wouldn't buy it.  Now that SLAYYY is growing like crazy...Lord I thank you...I will never forget those that stood 10 toes down with us from the beginning.
